<li id="cite_note-33"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/Lorenzo_Snow" title="Lorenzo Snow">Lorenzo Snow</a>'s couplet is more commonly quoted as: "As man now is, God once was: As God now is, man may be". See:<br />* <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLund1982" class="citation cs2"><a href="/wiki/Gerald_N._Lund" title="Gerald N. Lund">Lund, Gerald N.</a> (February 1982), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/ensign/1982/02/i-have-a-question">"I Have a Question: Is President Lorenzo Snow's oft-repeated statement—'As man now is, God once was; as God now is, man may be'—accepted as official doctrine by the Church?"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Ensign_(LDS_magazine)" title="Ensign (LDS magazine)">Ensign</a></i></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Ensign&amp;rft.atitle=I+Have+a+Question%3A+Is+President+Lorenzo+Snow%27s+oft-repeated+statement%E2%80%94%27As+man+now+is%2C+God+once+was%3B+as+God+now+is%2C+man+may+be%27%E2%80%94accepted+as+official+doctrine+by+the+Church%3F&amp;rft.date=1982-02&amp;rft.aulast=Lund&amp;rft.aufirst=Gerald+N.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fensign%2F1982%2F02%2Fi-have-a-question&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJudaism+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span>;<br />* <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMilletReynolds1998" class="citation cs2"><a href="/wiki/Robert_L._Millet" title="Robert L. Millet">Millet, Robert L.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Noel_B._Reynolds" title="Noel B. Reynolds">Reynolds, Noel B.</a> (1998), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://maxwellinstitute.byu.edu/publications/books/?bookid=45&amp;chapid=534">"Do Latter-day Saints believe that 